parts.text:
```json
{
  "application": "snapHiC",
  "details": {
    "software": "snapHiC",
    "dependencies": [
      "python (3.6+)",
      "cooler",
      "mpi4py (if parallelism is set to 'parallel')"
    ],
    "resources": {
      "hpc": {
        "queue": "hotel",
        "nodes": 5,
        "cores_per_node": 10,
        "walltime": "50:00:00",
        "memory": "100GB"
      },
      "other": {
        "parallelism": "parallel", "threaded", or "singleproc",
        "number_of_processors": "required only if parallelism is set to parallel or threaded",
        "input_directory": "directory containing input files",
        "suffix": "suffix of input files",
        "output_directory": "directory where output files will be stored",
        "chromosome_columns": "2 integer numbers, the column number of chromosomes in the input files",
        "position_columns": "2 integer numbers, the column number of mapped position of read-pairs",
        "chromosome_sizes_file": "path to the chrom.sizes file",
        "genome_id": "genomeID that will be used for genereation of '.hic' file",
        "filter_file": "regions to be filtered",
        "steps": "steps to run the pipeline",
        "prefix": "prefix for output file names",
        "rwr_method": "method for RWR computation"
      }
    }
  }
}
```
